                         DON'T MISS IT

                    Long Drivers of America

For you long-drive fans who missed the recent RE/MAX World
Long Drive Championship on ESPN, you can watch video replays
at www.longdrivers.com. You can also find out how to enter
next year if you feel you have the right stuff. Competitors
can choose from among four divisions: the Open Division,
open to everyone (pro, amateur, men or women); the Senior
Division for men 45 years old and up; the Women's Division
for females of any age; the Junior Division for boys and
girls under 18. Local qualifying begins in the spring and
continues throughout the summer. Entry fees are less than
the average greens fee, and you can receive a discount
along with other benefits if you become a member of Long
Drivers of America. Membership is $150 ($75 for juniors 17
and under).


